          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>Jan 25th</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><persName>Ceralvo Carroll</persName> by
                                        Miss</p>
                              <p><addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee> D.D.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dr sir—A Stranger as<lb/> I am I hope you will
                                        excuse the liberty<lb/> I have taken in addressing you for
                                        the<lb/> purpose of requesting a favour at your<lb/> hands.
                                        Whilst on a visit last summer<lb/> to my Brother in Law
                                                  <persName>Solomon<lb/> Eichelstiens</persName> I
                                        was introduced to the<lb/> "Occident" In Vol 8. No 12
                                                  <date>Veadar<lb/> 5611 Alias March 1851</date> my
                                        attention<lb/> was arrested by an article headed<lb/>
                                        "Letters On Christianity" By <persName>Isaac
                                        Wise</persName><lb/> at the close of said article he<lb/>
                                        proposes in his next to say something<lb/> about the origin
                                        of Christianity<lb/> and its dogma—That No I was not<lb/>
                                        able to obtain as <persName>Mr Eichelstien</persName>
                                        had<lb/> let someone have it Feeling a<lb/> very strong
                                        desire to see what the<lb/> views of an
                                                  <sic>inteligent</sic> and well infor<lb/>med Jew
                                        was on a subject that<lb/> Christian speakers and writers
                                        have<lb/> thus far failed to give me any satisfaction<lb/>
                                        on—I address you for that purpose<lb/> of <sic>geting</sic>
                                        it if you can or will</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>send it to me—indeed I would be<lb/> glad to have the whole series
                                        of <persName>Mr<lb/>
                                                  <del>wises</del> Wise's</persName> letters and
                                        will send<lb/> you the money if they are to be had<lb/> and
                                        I learn the sum requisite</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">But I am particularly anxious<lb/> to get that
                                        portion respecting the<lb/> Origin &amp;c of
                                        Christianity</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">By so doing you will<lb/> confer a lasting favour
                                        on one who<lb/> wants <hi rend="underline">more</hi> light
                                        on the mysteries<lb/> of Religion</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Very Respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">your friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">&amp; Obt Svt</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName role="author">C. C. Neight</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Address <persName>Ceralvo<lb/> Carroll</persName>
                                                  by<lb/>  <placeName>Mississippi</placeName></p>
